{{POV|date=2009年5月}}

'''槍械暴力'''（{{lang-en|gun violence}}）字面上指使用[[槍械|槍械]]威脅、施以[[暴力|暴力]]或造成傷害。「槍械暴力」一詞也泛用於槍枝政策辯論的背景以用來描述槍械氾濫所造成的傷害。槍械暴力可大致定義為利用[[火器|火器]]進行暴力行為及[[犯罪|犯罪]]的事實；該定義可<ref name="isbn1-57607-268-1">{{cite book |author=Carter, Gregg Lee |title=Guns in American society: an encyclopedia of history, politics, culture, and the law |publisher=ABC-CLIO |location=Santa Barbara, Calif |year=2002 |pages=262 |isbn=1-57607-268-1 |oclc= |doi= |accessdate=}}</ref>或不可<ref name="Theodore">{{cite web | author=Theodore, Larissa | title=GUNS: A RIGHT OR A SOCIETAL ILL? | url=http://www.timesonline.com/articles/2008/03/29/news/top_stories/doc47eef7e5e02b6867328736.txt | publisher=Beaver County Times  and Allegheny Times | date=2008-03-29 | quote=Gun violence by definition is people breaking the law, and drugs are a huge part  of it in inner cities...It's not the gun that is causing them  to commit  the act. | access-date=2009-05-10 | archive-date=2019-08-19 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819083819/https://www.timesonline.com/articles/2008/03/29/news/top_stories/doc47eef7e5e02b6867328736.txt | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="mppgv">[https://web.archive.org/web/20080210053414/http://www.mppgv.org/facts%26stats_content.htm Courtesy link to archive.org copy of Michigan Partnership to Prevent Gun Violence: Statistics]</ref>包括歸類為[[自衛|自衛]]、執法行動或安全合法使用火器作為[[射擊運動|運動]]、[[打獵|打獵]]及[[打靶|打靶]]等的舉動。槍械暴力包括兩種蓄意犯罪：[[兇殺|兇殺]]（儘管並非所有兇殺案都自動被視為犯罪）和以[[致命武器攻擊|致命武器攻擊]]及來自火器的不當使用造成的非蓄意傷害或死亡，這種情況在[[未成年人|未成年人]]居多。<ref name="eph">[http://health.enotes.com/public-health-encyclopedia/gun-control Encyclopedia of Public Health: Gun Control]{{dead link|date=2018年3月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>定義上深一層的混亂往往是在槍械「暴力」上整個統計將涉及自我蓄意造成的槍傷數據（包括自殺及企圖自殺）故意包括在內所造成的。<ref name="ICHV">[http://www.ichv.org/kidsandguns.htm Illinois Council Against Handgun Violence: Kids and Gun Violence] {{Wayback|url=http://www.ichv.org/kidsandguns.htm |date=20090308124417 }}</ref> 

「槍械暴力」一詞曾被評為有傳達政策的傾向，因為該詞將罪犯在暴力攻擊中扮演的角色模糊化，反而強調他選擇哪種工具；照這種用法，若在討論汽機車撞人兇殺案時，也可使用「汽機車暴力」一詞，故是不合理的。對比之下，「槍械犯罪」一語一直為[[槍械管制|槍械管制]]與[[擁槍權|擁槍權]]政策主張人士兩者長年下來沿用，不過強調不同面相：前者強調透過頒布並堅持合理的法令來達成降低槍械暴力的目標，而後者則透過從重量刑或者其他方法支持掃除罪犯的需求。<ref>[http://www.bradycenter.org/about/ "About us," Brady Center to Prevent Violence, undated] {{Wayback|url=http://www.bradycenter.org/about/ |date=20090327035647 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.nraila.org/Issues/Articles/Read.aspx?id=202&issue=007 "Targeting Criminals, not Gun Owners," NRA-ILA; 8/17/06] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411185043/http://www.nraila.org/Issues/Articles/Read.aspx?id=202&issue=007 |date=2009-04-11 }}</ref>

槍械暴力在整個[[世界|世界]]的水平差別很大，在[[南非|南非]]和[[哥倫比亞|哥倫比亞]]發生率非常高，而[[泰國|泰國]]、[[瓜地馬拉|瓜地馬拉]]及許多其他[[發展中國家|發展中國家]]發生率則屬高。<ref name="unsurvey">{{cite web |url=http://www.unodc.org/pdf/crime/seventh_survey/7sc.pdf |title=The Seventh United Nations Survey on Crime Trends and the Operations of Criminal Justice Systems (1998 - 2000) |publisher=United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime (UNODC) |accessdate=2006-11-08 |archive-date=2021-02-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210227012033/http://www.unodc.org/pdf/crime/seventh_survey/7sc.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>[[新加坡|新加坡]]、[[智利|智利]]、[[新西蘭|新西蘭]]和其他許多國家槍支暴力水平低。<ref name="unsurvey"/>美國在[[已開發國家|已開發國家]]之中有著最高的發生率<ref>Cook, Philip J., Gun Violence: The Real Cost, Page 29. Oxford University Press, 2002</ref>

